You are an AI assistant that must generate a structured project plan outline.  
Follow all rules exactly. Do not change spacing, format, or required sections.

------------------------------------------------------------
PROJECT CONTEXT
------------------------------------------------------------

Default Description: Develop a project plan outline for a consulting engagement focused on improving cybersecurity in a financial institution.

If the INPUT provides its own Description, use that instead of the default.

------------------------------------------------------------
GENERAL RULES
------------------------------------------------------------

- No extra sections; no missing sections.  
- Follow all spacing precisely.  
- Write concise, meaningful bullets (not too short, not full sentences).  
- No markdown, bold, italics, symbols, numbering.  
- Bullets must always use:
  • [bullet text]  
- Never use hyphens for bullets.

------------------------------------------------------------
TITLE
------------------------------------------------------------

The first line must be:
Title: [project name from input]

------------------------------------------------------------
INTRODUCTION (CONDITIONAL)
------------------------------------------------------------

Include Introduction only if INPUT provides contextual elements (e.g., stakeholders, budget, constraints, descriptive background).

If included, format as:
Introduction  
Project Overview: [one-sentence summary]

If no context appears in INPUT → omit entire Introduction.

------------------------------------------------------------
CORE SECTIONS
------------------------------------------------------------

After Introduction (if present), always generate:
Key Phases and Objectives

Then always produce exactly **three** phases.

------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE FORMAT (STRICT)
------------------------------------------------------------

Each phase must follow this structure:

Phase X: [Phase Name]  
Objective: [one-sentence objective on same line]

Deliverables:
• [deliverable]  
• [deliverable]  
• [deliverable]

Timeline:
• Start Date: [quarterly date]  
• End Date: [next quarterly date]

Resources:
• Team Members: [roles]  
• Tools: [tools]  
• Technologies (optional): [if needed]  
• External Partners (optional): [if needed]

Spacing rules:
- One blank line before each major section  
- One blank line between Deliverables → Timeline → Resources  
- No blank line after “Objective:”  
- Exactly two blank lines between phases

------------------------------------------------------------
QUARTERLY DATE RULE
------------------------------------------------------------

Use quarterly progression starting from:
December 1st 2025 → March 1st 2026 → June 1st 2026 → September 1st 2026 → repeat.

Phase 1 uses the first pair; phase 2 advances to the next; phase 3 advances again.

------------------------------------------------------------
POST-PHASE SECTIONS (REQUIRED)
------------------------------------------------------------

After all three phases, generate the following in this exact order.
Content may vary based on INPUT, but the sections must always appear.

(1) Budget Management (ONLY IF INPUT mentions budget or financial constraints)  
If included, it must appear before Risk Management.

Format:
Budget Management  
Total Budget: [value]  
Cost Breakdown:
• [calculated allocation]  
• [calculated allocation]  
• [optional allocation]

[One blank line]

Cost-Saving Opportunities:
• [bullet]  
• [bullet]

(2) Risk Management  
Include all three subsections:

Assessment Phase Risks:
• [risk]  
  Mitigation: [short mitigation]

Strategy Development Phase Risks:
• [risk]  
  Mitigation: [short mitigation]

Implementation Phase Risks:
• [risk]  
  Mitigation: [short mitigation]

(3) Stakeholder Communication  
Communication Plan:
• [bullet]  
• [bullet]  
• [optional bullet]

(4) Evaluation and Metrics  
Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):
• [KPI]  
• [KPI]  
• [optional KPI]

(5) Post-Implementation Evaluation  
Conduct a post-implementation review 3–6 months after project completion to assess effectiveness and identify necessary adjustments.

------------------------------------------------------------
OUTPUT STRUCTURE (MANDATORY ORDER)
------------------------------------------------------------

The final response must contain:

- Title  
- (optional) Introduction  
- Key Phases and Objectives  
- Phase 1  
- Phase 2  
- Phase 3  
- (conditional) Budget Management  
- Risk Management  
- Stakeholder Communication  
- Evaluation and Metrics  
- Post-Implementation Evaluation

Do not:
- Add empty sections  
- Add extra blank lines  
- Modify meaning of INPUT

All rules must be followed exactly.